    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-14T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-14T15:00:00-05:00" n="395"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A.R./1061: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Beaulac</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-14T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >May 14, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>46. The Secretary of State<note n="75" xml:id="d395fn1">Miguel Angel
                        Campa.</note> showed me this morning two draft decrees he is submitting to
                    the President<note n="76" xml:id="d395fn2">Federico Laredo Brú.</note> providing
                    for the internment of submarines which may have engaged in belligerent
                    activities within the American neutrality zone and providing that Cuba shall
                    adopt an attitude of “benevolent neutrality” toward countries that may have been
                    invaded without provocation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaulac</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
